{
  "page": "Storm King",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Durran_Elenei.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/57/Durran_Elenei.jpg/300px-Durran_Elenei.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"532\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/5/57/Durran_Elenei.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Durran_Elenei.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Godsgrief\" title=\"Durran Godsgrief\">Durran Godsgrief</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a>, from <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i> Blu-ray</div></div></div>\n<p>The title of <b>Storm King</b> was held by the ancient <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">Durrandon</a> kings, who ruled the <b>Kingdom of the Storm</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> most of which is now the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> and at one point included the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a>, and the eastern part of the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Storm_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Storm Kings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Argilac_the_Arrogant\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Argilac the Arrogant</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#The_Laughing_Storm\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Laughing Storm</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_Storm_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Storm Kings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Storm_King&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Storm_Kings\">Storm Kings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Storm_King&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Storm Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The first of the line was <a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Godsgrief\" title=\"Durran Godsgrief\">Durran Godsgrief</a>, who according to legends built <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> and won the love of <a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a>, the daughter of the <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_god\" title=\"Sea god\">sea god</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Goddess_of_the_wind\" title=\"Goddess of the wind\">goddess of the wind</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Storm Kings established a powerful kingdom, and the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">Durrandons</a> extended their control north to <a href=\"/index.php/Massey%27s_Hook\" title=\"Massey&#39;s Hook\">Massey's Hook</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Bay_of_Crabs\" title=\"Bay of Crabs\">Bay of Crabs</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> west into the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Dornish Marches</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and south to <a href=\"/index.php/Cape_Wrath\" title=\"Cape Wrath\">Cape Wrath</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Arlan III Durrandon\">Arlan III Durrandon</a>, the stormlands claimed the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> after the downfall of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Teague\" title=\"House Teague\">House Teague</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> King <a href=\"/index.php/Arrec_Durrandon\" title=\"Arrec Durrandon\">Arrec Durrandon</a> was defeated by <a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_Hoare\" title=\"Harwyn Hoare\">Harwyn Hoare</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"King of the Iron Islands\">King of the Iron Islands</a>, in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Fairmarket\" title=\"Battle at Fairmarket\">battle at Fairmarket</a>, ending three centuries of Storm King rule over the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Argilac_the_Arrogant\">Argilac the Arrogant</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Storm_King&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Argilac the Arrogant\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Century_of_Blood\" title=\"Century of Blood\">Century of Blood</a>, the militant <a href=\"/index.php/Tigers_(Volantis)\" title=\"Tigers (Volantis)\">tigers</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> attacked <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a> after taking <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a>. The Storm King <a href=\"/index.php/Argilac_Durrandon\" title=\"Argilac Durrandon\">Argilac Durrandon</a> joined the <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord of Braavos</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Lord of Dragonstone\">Lord of Dragonstone</a>, in aiding <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a> in Tyrosh's defense, however, allowing Lys and Myr to rebel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Argilac defeated a Volantene host in the <a href=\"/index.php/Disputed_Lands\" title=\"Disputed Lands\">Disputed Lands</a> which was attempting to retake Myr.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The last Storm King, Argilac the Arrogant, was slain in the <a href=\"/index.php/Last_Storm\" title=\"Last Storm\">Last Storm</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Orys_Baratheon\" title=\"Orys Baratheon\">Orys Baratheon</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Argella_Durrandon\" title=\"Argella Durrandon\">Argella Durrandon</a> declared herself Storm Queen after her father's death, but the men of <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> turned her over to Orys's camp.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Orys wed Argella and took Argilac's colors and words as his own during <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, founding <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon\" title=\"House Baratheon\">House Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> King Aegon granted Storm's End to Orys and named him <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Stormlands\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Stormlands\">Lord Paramount of the Stormlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Laughing_Storm\">The Laughing Storm</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Storm_King&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Laughing Storm\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_Targaryen\" title=\"Duncan Targaryen\">Duncan Targaryen</a> married <a href=\"/index.php/Jenny_of_Oldstones\" title=\"Jenny of Oldstones\">Jenny of Oldstones</a>, breaking his betrothal with the daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Lyonel_Baratheon\" title=\"Lyonel Baratheon\">Lyonel Baratheon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Lord of Storm&#39;s End\">Lord of Storm's End</a>. The outraged Lyonel renounced his fealty to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> and declared himself Storm King. A <a href=\"/index.php/Lyonel_Baratheon%27s_rebellion\" title=\"Lyonel Baratheon&#39;s rebellion\">short and bloody rebellion</a> followed, which ended when Lyonel, the Laughing Storm, yielded to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> during a <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by battle</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_baratheon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_baratheon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Storm_Kings\">Known Storm Kings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Storm_King&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Storm Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Argilac_Durrandon.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/86/Argilac_Durrandon.png/300px-Argilac_Durrandon.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"392\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/8/86/Argilac_Durrandon.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Argilac_Durrandon.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Argilac_Durrandon\" title=\"Argilac Durrandon\">Argilac Durrandon</a> the last Storm King, from <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i> Blu-ray</div></div></div>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Godsgrief\" title=\"Durran Godsgrief\">Durran Godsgrief</a>, a legendary figure from the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a> who built <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> and founded <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran II Durrandon\">Durran II</a>, the Devout</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Durrandon_(Bronze-Axe)\" title=\"Durran Durrandon (Bronze-Axe)\">Durran Bronze-Axe</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Durrandon_(the_Dour)\" title=\"Durran Durrandon (the Dour)\">Durran the Dour</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Durrandon_(the_Ravenfriend)\" title=\"Durran Durrandon (the Ravenfriend)\">Durran the Ravenfriend</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Durrandon_(the_Young)\" title=\"Durran Durrandon (the Young)\">Durran the Young</a>, also called \"the Butcher Boy.\"</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Durrandon_(the_Fair)\" title=\"Durran Durrandon (the Fair)\">Durran the Fair</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Erich_Durrandon_(the_Sailmaker)\" title=\"Erich Durrandon (the Sailmaker)\">Erich III</a>, the Sailmaker</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_X_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran X Durrandon\">Durran X</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Monfryd_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Monfryd I Durrandon\">Monfryd I</a>, the Mighty</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_XI_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran XI Durrandon\">Durran XI</a>, the Dim'</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Barron_Durrandon\" title=\"Barron Durrandon\">Barron the Beautiful</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durwald_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Durwald I Durrandon\">Durwald I</a>, the Fat</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Morden_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Morden II Durrandon\">Morden II</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ronard_Storm\" title=\"Ronard Storm\">Ronard Storm</a>, the Bastard</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Erich_VII_Durrandon\" title=\"Erich VII Durrandon\">Erich VII</a>, the Unready</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Qarlton_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Qarlton II Durrandon\">Qarlton II</a>, the Conqueror</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Qarlton_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Qarlton III Durrandon\">Qarlton III</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Monfryd_V_Durrandon\" title=\"Monfryd V Durrandon\">Monfryd V</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Baldric_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Baldric I Durrandon\">Baldric I</a>, the Cunning</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_XXI_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran XXI Durrandon\">Durran XXI</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Cleoden_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Cleoden I Durrandon\">Cleoden I</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Maldon_IV_Durrandon\" title=\"Maldon IV Durrandon\">Maldon IV</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_XXIV_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran XXIV Durrandon\">Durran XXIV</a>, called Half-blood.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ormund_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Ormund III Durrandon\">Ormund III</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Durran_Durrandon_(The_Third)\" title=\"Durran Durrandon (The Third)\">Durran the Third</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-DurranThird_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DurranThird-12\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Arlan I Durrandon\">Arlan I</a>, the Avenger</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Arlan III Durrandon\">Arlan III</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Arrec_Durrandon\" title=\"Arrec Durrandon\">Arrec</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_V_Durrandon\" title=\"Arlan V Durrandon\">Arlan V</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Argilac_Durrandon\" title=\"Argilac Durrandon\">Argilac the Arrogant</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Argella_Durrandon\" title=\"Argella Durrandon\">Argella</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Argella_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Argella-13\">&#91;N 2&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lyonel_Baratheon\" title=\"Lyonel Baratheon\">Lyonel Baratheon</a>, the Laughing Storm<sup id=\"cite_ref-Lyonel_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Lyonel-14\">&#91;N 3&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-